    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I understand what drives value in this corridor. Doolandella buyers compare your property directly against Forest Lake and Ellen Grove, and the campaign needs to position correctly within that comparison set from day one. Overpriced listings in this market do not attract patience, they attract nothing.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The suburb's residential streets sit alongside Forest Lake's leisure amenity, including the lake itself and the established parkland network that runs through this western corridor. Modern brick and tile homes on flat, usable blocks attract the clearest buyer demand, particularly from young families who are buying their first or second home in the area. The Centenary Motorway provides direct access to the CBD and to employment hubs at Richlands and Wacol, and that transport access is a genuine selling point for commuting buyers.
    </p>
