          Is Doolandella a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Doolandella remains an accessible entry point into western Brisbane's family market, with consistent demand from first home buyers and young families. Values here are influenced by Forest Lake comparables, and the suburb's modern estate stock appeals to buyers who want freestanding homes on usable blocks.</p>
